quote: Coming together is a beginning; keeping together is progress; working together is success.
author: Henry Ford

quote: Waiting is erotic
author: Irène Némirovsky,  Suite Française

quote: What comes, is called.
author: Ki Longfellow,  Flow Down Like Silver: Hypatia of Alexandria

quote: Beyond myself, somewhere, I wait for my arrival.
author: Octavio Paz,  The Collected Poems, 1957-1987

quote: Even this late it happens:the coming of love, the coming of light.
author: Mark Strand,  Selected Poems

quote: What comes, when it comes, will be what it is.
author: Alberto Caeiro,  The Collected Poems of Alberto Caeiro

quote: If you are a dreamer, come in,If you are a dreamer, a wisher, a liar,A hope-er, a pray-er, a magic bean buyer...If you're a pretender, come sit by my fireFor we have some flax-golden tales to spin. Come in!Come in!

quote: I've gone to prepare a place for youBut I will come back again.
author: Anonymous,  Holy Bible: King James Version

quote: I am ready for whatever's coming. I expect nothing but to be let down or turned away. I am alone. Goddamn. The shit hurts sometimes, but I realize what I am, what I have become.
author: Henry Rollins

quote: Can I come in?No! I'm in a towel!I'm blind!

quote: All hope abandon, ye who enter here!
author: Dante Alighieri

quote: I rather now strive to reach rather than wait to receive!
author: Jonathan Anthony Burkett

quote: Death twitches my ear;'Live,' he says... 'I'm coming.
author: Virgil

quote: Being ready is everything.
author: Caroline Gerardo,  Toxic Assets

quote: By daily dying, I have come to be.
author: Theodore Roethke,  The Collected Poems

quote: My toes are going to come,"-MariannThe Night Owl
author: Emma Holly,  Hot Blooded

quote: Little by little, one travels far
author: J.R.R. Tolkien

quote: If something is going to happen to me, I want to be there.
author: Albert Camus,  The Stranger

author: Edna St. Vincent Millay,  The Harp-Weaver and Other Poems

quote: Past, I am letting you go. Future, I will see you tomorrow. Present, I love you, live in you, celebrate you, and will never let you go.
author: Debasish Mridha

quote: If you want me, you’d better hurry. Act now, supplies are limited.
author: Jarod Kintz,  This Book is Not FOR SALE

quote: The Coming of LightEven this late it happens:the coming of love, the coming of light. You wake and the candles are lit as if by themselves, stars gather, dreams pour into your pillows, sending up warm bouquets of air.Even this late the bones of the body shine and tomorrow’s dust flares into breath.

quote: Dev-"Come in peace or leave in pieces
author: Sherrilyn Kenyon,  Bad Moon Rising

quote: I have come from the End of the World. From the River of Dreams, through the gauntlet and the Briar and the Deep Wyld, in order to stand before you today. I have but one request—to take my place at your side. To resume my duty as your knight, and to protect you and your kingdom for as long as I draw breath.

quote: Becoming hurts.
author: Kat Howard

quote: Reach for the stars.
author: Christa McAuliffe

quote: I will follow you to the ends of the world.
author: Khaled Hosseini,  A Thousand Splendid Suns

quote: Laters, baby.
author: E.L. James,  Fifty Shades of Grey

quote: I’ve got a way with love. Away with love.
author: Jarod Kintz,  Love quotes for the ages. Specifically ages 18-81.

quote: Morning dew upon the grass,glistening in the sun.Yesterday’s gone,tomorrow may come,but this day has begun.

quote: Love waits patiently. In the lobby. I’ll be with you as soon as I can.
author: Jarod Kintz,  Love quotes for the ages. Specifically ages 18-81.

quote: When you anxiously await to emerge from deep darkness, you will realize the beauty of light.

quote: If you are a dreamer come in
author: Shel Silverstein

quote: All is flux
author: Heraclitus,  The Fragments of the Work of Heraclitus of Ephesus on Nature with an Introduction Historical and Critical

quote: I may be going nowhere, but what a ride.

quote: So you want me to go to a human orgy, where I will not be welcome, and you want us to leave before I get to enjoy myself? ~Eric Northman

quote: You came from love, to live in love, to give away love, and to become love.
